<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 30 at 7:31PM MDT until June 30 at 8:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 815 PM MDT
FOR NORTHERN PROWERS COUNTY...
At 730 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles west of
Granada, or 9 miles southeast of Lamar, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. Locally heavy
rain was also occurring with this storm.
Locations impacted include...
Lamar, Holly, Granada, Wiley, Hartman and Bristol.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
